# OpenClaw UI Design System Integration Protocol v1.0

## 0. Objective

Integrate a unified UI design system into the existing OpenClaw-based platform to:

* Improve visual consistency across Portal apps
* Increase AI-generated UI quality (Antigravity / Codex / Claude Code)
* Reduce UI rework loops
* Enable reusable component-based generation

This protocol MUST be implemented without breaking existing services.

---

## 1. Target Environment

Root:
D:\Clawdbot_Docker_20260125

Key Components:

* Portal (nginx): http://localhost:8088
* Antigravity: UI/code generation
* Codex CLI: implementation & repair
* Ollama / Gemini (via LiteLLM): LLM backend

UI Locations:

* /portal/apps/*
* standalone HTML tools (GD&T viewer etc.)

---

## 2. Core Concept

AI must NOT generate arbitrary UI.

Instead:
→ All UI must conform to a strict design system

This system will be enforced via:

1. design_system.json
2. reusable UI components
3. strict prompt constraints

---

## 3. File Structure (MANDATORY)

Create:

/portal/design_system/
├── design_system.json
├── ui_rules.md
├── components/
│      ├── card.html
│      ├── button.html
│      ├── input.html
│      └── layout.html
└── templates/
├── dashboard.html
└── form.html

---

## 4. design_system.json

Create the following EXACT file:

{
"spacing": [4, 8, 16, 24, 32],
"radius": "rounded-2xl",
"shadow": "shadow-md",
"font": {
"title": "text-xl font-semibold",
"body": "text-base",
"caption": "text-sm text-gray-500"
},
"colors": {
"primary": "blue-600",
"secondary": "gray-700",
"danger": "red-500",
"background": "gray-50"
},
"layout": {
"card_padding": "p-4",
"gap": "gap-4"
}
}

---

## 5. UI Rules (STRICT)

Create ui_rules.md:

### MANDATORY RULES

1. NO inline styles
2. Tailwind classes ONLY
3. MUST use spacing scale (4/8/16/24/32)
4. ALL cards must use:

   * rounded-2xl
   * shadow-md
   * p-4
5. Font hierarchy must follow design_system.json
6. DO NOT invent colors
7. DO NOT mix different padding sizes randomly
8. Layout must use flex or grid
9. Every UI must look consistent with Portal

---

